de.boereck.matcher

Interface ResultCaseMatcher<I,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - type of the input object to be matched
    O - type of the result object returned from the case found
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    EagerResultCaseMatcher<I,O>

    public interface ResultCaseMatcher<I,O>

    This interface is used to define cases that can be used to found a given object and define associated functions that are executed when a case matches for the given object and return a result value. The result value will be returned by closing methods. See below which methods of this class are closing methods.
    The object to be checked has to be provided during creation of the instance. Only the action of one of the given cases that matches will be executed.

    The case de.boereck.matcher interface does not give a guarantee if the cases are checked in the order they are specified. It is also not guaranteed that remaining cases are evaluated when a matching case was found. Implementations may even execute the found checks and actions asynchronously. This has to be clarified by the factory method providing the instance or by sub-types providing a stricter API.

    It is also not defined if the evaluation of case predicates or functions is done eager when a case method is called or lazy when a closing method is called (starting the evaluation of cases). This interface does not declare any closing methods, sub-types may define their own closing methods.

      • caseOf

        <T> ResultCaseMatcher<I,O> caseOf(Class<T> clazz,
                                  Function<? super T,? extends O> f)
                           throws NullPointerException
        Defines a case that checks if the input object is instance of the given class. If the case is determined to be the matching case, the provided function f will be called with the input object casted to the type the case is checking for. The result of the function will be the result of the case found.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type the input object is checked to be instance of
        Parameters:
        clazz - Type the input object is checked to be instance of
        f - function that will be executed (with input object as parameter) when the case is determined to be the matching one. The result of this function will be the result of the case found.
        Returns:
        instance of ResultCaseMatcher (maybe same as same object as this) to define further cases.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - might be thrown if either parameter clazz or f is null.

      • caseOf

        ResultCaseMatcher<I,O> caseOf(boolean test,
                              Function<? super I,? extends O> f)
                       throws NullPointerException

        This method defines a case that applies if the given boolean parameter test is true. If the case is determined to be the matching case, the provided consumer function will be called with the input value. The result of the function will be the result of the matching case.

        Be aware that the expression that evaluates to the value of the test parameter will always be evaluated, even if a previous case matched already. It is recommended to use caseOf(Predicate, Function) or caseOf(BooleanSupplier, Function) instead. If the runtime cost of the check is little this method, however, can produce more readable code.

        Parameters:
        test - boolean value that determines if this case is a found and if the consumer should be invoked.
        f - will be invoked with the object to be matched if the test parameter is true.
        Returns:
        instance of ResultCaseMatcher (which might the same as this object) to define further cases.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - might be thrown if parameter f is null.

      • caseObj

        <T> ResultCaseMatcher<I,O> caseObj(Function<? super I,Optional<T>> p,
                                   Function<? super T,? extends O> f)
                            throws NullPointerException
        Defines a case that matches if the function p returns a non empty Optional when called with the input value. If the case is determined to be the matching case, the provided function f will be called with the the object that is wrapped in the optional returned by function p. The result of the consumer function will be the overall result of the case found.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of object extracted by function p.
        Parameters:
        p - function that returns an optional that indicates if the case is a found, when the optional is not empty.
        f - will be called if the function p returns an non-empty optional and the case is determined to be the matching case. The consumer will be called with the value wrapped in the optional object. The result of the function will be the result of the case found.
        Returns:
        instance of ResultCaseMatcher (which might the same as this object) to define further cases.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - might be thrown if either parameter p or f is null.
